Program: Discovery
Title: The Great Dinosaur Hunt - part two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxtz
Last Broadcast Date: 17 May 2001
The first in a three-part selected history of those who discovered the dinosaurs The story of Baron Franz Nopcsa of Albania, his pioneering work and his contribution to paleontology. Many of his ideas are used in modern dinosaur science.